The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for answer triggering, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves similarity and coverage measures, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
